g.text: The Deserter: "Three weeks ago, when the rich hag came in on her galley. Her honour guard came in tow."
The Deserter: "After she was gone." He nods.
Suggestion: And now he longs to see her covered in blood.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Past the Feld building, on the coast? What was she doing there?"
The Deserter: "The sun came up, her hair was like cobwebs. She smoked more fags and snorted a line of whatever shit she was on. Right there..." he shakes his head. "She needed it just to move."
You: "Are you sure? I checked the submersible. There was nothing there."
"Are you sure? We checked the submersible. There was nothing there."
You: "What did it say her name was -- in the passport?"
You: "Where was this submersible, looks like the investigation missed it?"
The Deserter: "Mhm," he smacks his lips. "Bending like a bow against the glass..."
Kim Kitsuragi: "But *that* nook too?" The lieutenant does not let you finish.
The Deserter: "Why would I need that trash?" He looks to the reeds, confused. "I'm not going to Villiers..."
The Deserter: "It didn't say *Klaasje* in there..." He shakes his head.
Physical Instrument: You're a bad detective. Lazy and bad.
Rhetoric: There! He's already admitted to it! Just ask...
The Deserter: "That fucking whore..." He waves his hand, with sudden anger. Something comes over him...
The Deserter: He nods. "Made a little love-nest up there. Sweaty linen and bottles they would use for god knows what... I saw other men there too, but I can't be sure. Even a woman once."

Shivers: Inside, in a cell, a young woman is withdrawing from amphetamines, barbiturates and alcohol. All at once. While two men in brown suits wave ICP badges at a young policeman. She hears the door open...
Shivers: On the platform a young woman is withdrawing from amphetamines, barbiturates and alcohol. Yet still she smiles among the crowd, fading from your mind's eye...
The Deserter: "Wrinkled up whore," he nods.
Half Light: An anger too, in addition to loneliness.
You: "You climbed, right? You *climbed* behind her window, like the CRAB-MAN?"
The Deserter: "What are you talking about -- 'crab-man'?" He waves you off with a cough.
The Deserter: "Like that too, yes," he nods. "Bending like a bow against the glass..."
The Deserter: "I don't really know. I was there one night and she was crying, like a child -- in the corner of her room, on the floor. Like she does sometimes...."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did you keep what was in it? When we found the submersible it was empty."
You: "Did you keep the materials? When I found the submersible it was empty."
The Deserter: "Yes. After she'd gone. It was a submersible. Well made, actually..."
Composure: A strange confusion comes over him from time to time. Some kind of aberration of the nervous system?
Reaction Speed: He must have... climbed to the roof maybe?
You: "How did you get close enough to see her bruises, Mr. Dros?"
You: "You climbed, right? You *climbed* behind her window?"
Physical Instrument: As you should be, son, this is pitiful. Make up for it now!
Kim Kitsuragi: ... then at the man. "How did you get in there? The hidden pinball workshop?"
Physical Instrument: Of course it's not *okay*. Make up for it now, maximum performance!
The Deserter: "Maybe..." He lowers his head and just stares at the logs. "I told you, I have holes in my brain now. I wouldn't just sit here waiting for you..."
The Deserter: "Maybe..." He lowers his head and just stares at the logs. "I have these... holes in my brain now. I wouldn't just sit here waiting for you..."
You: "She got away. I don't know where she is."
"She got away. We don't know where she is."
The Deserter: "Good for her..." He looks to the city and nods: "That girl kept staring into the scope, you know -- in the end. This last week, kept staring at the island..."
You: "She got away, but she led me here first. She figured out someone was watching her from the seafort."
"She got away, but she led us here first. She figured out someone was watching her from the seafort."
The Deserter: "Gone..." He looks to the city and nods: "I knew it. She kept staring into the scope this last week. At the island, like she knew...." He sighs.
The Deserter: "Her..." He repeats, staring at the ashes -- then at the reeds. There's a twitch in the corner of his eye.
Cuno: "It was about bitches." The boy nods grimly.
Esprit de Corps: There -- motive, detective. We have it.
Shivers: ...and knows it's over. They've come for her. Outside it's springtime, the river flows blue and green into the Bay of Martinaise.

Shivers: Midtown, across the bay of Revachol. Cold rain falls on forty-story towers. Above them -- Lausanne Central Aerodrome; a cocoon suspended in the grey sky by a web of suspension wiring, encircled by hybrid aircraft.
You: "This is the so-called soucriant again, right? Joyce?"
Jump to: [The Deserter: ""Wrinkled up whore," he nods."]
Kim Kitsuragi: "How could you see what she looked like? You said it was dark."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Sloppy, we should have gotten her to tell us about this..." the lieutenant mutters to himself. "Did you take the documents?"
The Deserter: "No. I put them back. Why would I take them, I'm not going to Falne..." He seems confused, momentarily. "Or... I mean..."
You: How does he know those minute details about her body?
Kim Kitsuragi: "You could tell she was a *spook* from the documents?"
The Deserter: "She had different colour hair on the photo, and glasses. *Forged*. Some sordid, bourgeois affair. I've heard about this kind of thing on the radio..."
Interfacing: And he found use for it -- a spare key, like the one hanging behind the Union box window.
The Deserter: "There's..." he sighs, "there's nothing to hold on to, only this... It's not enough."
Perception (Sight): The coals of his eyes glisten suddenly, like stones dripping with water. Is he crying?
The Deserter: "The day after I'd killed him."
You: "Did you leave the dried May bells behind her window?"
The Deserter: "I did. I shouldn't have. It was a mistake..." A tremor passes the right side of his face.
Visual Calculus: The bruises. Can you make that out in a scope?
You: "How did you see all this. The bruises; that she was beaten?"
The Deserter: "That kind of thing is fine by the Party so it's fine by me. But it goes to show you..." He just shakes his head.
Rhetoric: Seems like the answer was yes.
Kim Kitsuragi: "We could get more..." the lieutenant uses the opportunity to tell you -- in a lowered voice. "We've got him talking..."
Logic: Who knows what he's seen and done over the years?
Shivers: ...and knows it's over. They've come for her. Outside night falls, the river flows by, treacle black into the Bay of Martinaise.

Shivers: On the platform a young woman is withdrawing from amphetamines, barbiturates and alcohol. Yet still she smiles among the crowd, among the great ghost of the city she's leaving -- for another, far south.

Shivers: Midtown, across the bay of Revachol. Snow falls on forty-story towers. Above them -- Lausanne Central Aerodrome; a cocoon suspended in the snowy sky by a web of suspension wiring, encircled by hybrid aircraft.
Empathy: Good luck, Harry, she thinks. You need something *good* for this...
Electrochemistry: Some strange glandular process takes place in him at the thought. Like yeast rising...
Rhetoric: Joyce... he means Joyce again.
You: "Let's talk about something else for now."
The Deserter: "They moved into a deserted apartment above the roundabout." He nods toward the city. "Radio equipment out for all to see -- reactionary radio playing. Sloppy and drunk."
The Deserter: "I've seen their kind during the Landing. Those Occidental and Mesque falangues weren't conscripts -- boys, like us. They were wights. All they know is to destroy and hurt."
The Deserter: "Hiding something in the water. She had a fag after she'd done it. I was up in the ruins there -- she couldn't see me, but I could see her. Smoking... she was nervous, but not scared."
You: "First -- you could tell she was a *spook* from the documents?"
The Deserter: "She had different colour hair on the photo -- and glasses. *Forged*. Some sort of sordid, bourgeois affair. I've heard about this kind of thing on the radio..."
The Deserter: "She practically breastfed that man. You wouldn't believe the things she let him do to her..." He shakes his head and stares at the ashes.

The Deserter: "You turn it on inside and it gets so dark out you can't see a man looking in. I learned that in the Twenties when they were still hunting me. I've seen people do *some* shit, but..." He keeps shaking his head.
The Deserter: "I can just walk in the hostel now, after a good wash. They all think I'm an antisocial, a vagrant. Closing hour is a good time. The kitchen's empty then."
You: "One more thing, Mr. Dros -- the dried flowers. On the roof."
You: "How did you see all this. The bruises, that she was beaten?"
The Deserter: "Heh..." He shakes his silver-grey head.
You: "I'm not like that. I don't think like that."
You: "I hate women too, you know."

The Deserter: "True, there is something bourgeois about women..." He nods. "The weak are more vulnerable to exploitation by capital, unless they rise up in arms, which the likes of her..." He shakes his head.
You: "I am not at liberty to say."

Shivers: Smaller. Distant. Hidden. Not like the great chandelier she sees sparkle in the dusk below her. Streets, towers, tenements and cold water; and across the water -- a dark strip of ruins barely visible, if she didn't squint her eyes...
The Deserter: "You're delusional. There's nothing to *see* in the soul of the bourgeois woman. It's the same as the surface -- sick hedonism and desperation."
You: "She did deserve a good punishing."
The Deserter: "Where is she?" The old man looks at you. "I haven't seen her there for days."
"Where is she... that *Klaasje*?" The old man looks at you. "I haven't seen her there for days."
Physical Instrument: *Enough*. Take him in. Bend his arms behind his back and end this.
Suggestion: You could get more out of him... He likes talking.
The Deserter: The old man has fallen silent, staring at your feet. The burnt logs in the fire are moist from the sea air.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did you keep the documents in it?"
Cuno: "Yeah." Cuno nods knowingly. "The lightning gets shit going. Speedfreaks fuckin' in the bushes..."
Savoir Faire: He must knows his way around a creaky floorboard and a rusty hinge on a door...
You: "Ever see her through a window, on a roof?"
Hand/Eye Coordination: The calibre of bullet he used does not do that kind of damage.
You: "Some kind of hidden container on the coast? You looked into it?

The Deserter: "Jealousy is a reactionary concept. I didn't *like* the reaver enjoying himself -- drugged out, soothed in the arms of a young woman. I wanted him to die so he could not enjoy life anymore."
You: "What do you think she hid there?"
The Deserter: "You can't see that through a scope. It's just a blur there..." He shakes his silver-grey head.
You: "You've been through the secret route behind the Whirling-in-Rags." (Move on.)
"You've been through the secret route behind the Whirling-in-Rags. Those were *your* footprints. You just changed your shoes." (Move on.)
"You've been through the secret route behind the Whirling-in-Rags. Those were *your* footprints." (Move on.)
The Deserter: "I've been through *all* of Martinaise -- every nook and cranny."
Kim Kitsuragi: You hear the familiar scribble of the lieutenant's pen. A quick glance at you...
The Deserter: "I can just walk in there now, after a good wash -- I told you they think I'm an antisocial. Closing hour is a good time. The kitchen's empty."
The Deserter: Neither does he. He lowers his head, like a sunflower on a withered stalk.
The Deserter: "Yes. Over the years. It's not un-proletarian to feel something."
Volition: It's as if something *put* the thought there. To leave the flowers.
You: "Something *put* the thought in you. A compulsion."
The Deserter: "Man needs to feel something else. In this fight, it helps if you have your eye on something there," he looks to the city. "It's weakness, I know."
"Man needs to feel something else. It helps if you have your eye on something -- there," he looks to the city where the lights sparkle. "Something pretty. It's weakness, I know."
Logic: Also, a little inconsistency here -- he was surprised to hear her name Klaasje, before. Would he not have seen it on the documents?
Logic: A little inconsistency -- he was surprised to hear her name Klaasje, before. Would he not have seen it on the documents?
The Deserter: "The world is insane..." He raises his gaze. Something glimmers in there. Then it's gone.
Inland Empire: See you tomorrow, Harry. Her voice rings in the evening air, burning...
Esprit de Corps: "He's there, doing... *what* exactly I don't know," Satellite-Officer Vicquemare points at the ruins. "Behind that anti-aircraft-something. That's why we can't see him."
Rhetoric: He knew she knows. She was looking at the island, figuring it out -- day by day, cigarette by cigarette...
Esprit de Corps: As the men go, Patrol Officer Minot looks back over her shoulder -- at the crumbling fortification in the snowfall, like a rotten tooth rising out of the water...
Esprit de Corps: As the men go, Patrol Officer Minot looks back over her shoulder -- at the crumbling fortification, like a rotten tooth rising out of the water...
The Deserter: "I could see they've returned now. To show their real face -- the face they don't dare show their bourgeois voters back on Mundi, with their families and polyester clothes..."
The Deserter: "So don't you sermonize me, you racist shithole." He adds. "It's still bourgeois when the bourgeois does it. Fiddling with their sexual organs..."
You: "Khm..." (Cough.) "Moving on -- the victim arrives some time after her..."
"Khm..." (Cough.) "Moving on -- the negotiator's *security detail* arrives shortly after..."
You: "Whore. Good strong word. I use it often myself."
You: "What is it with these *whores* and *pederasts*... aren't you a communist?"
You: "Did you have feelings for that woman?"
You: "Moving on -- did you continue watching her after this?" (Proceed.)
Esprit de Corps: One more loose end down. We're doing this, detective.
Inland Empire: Is it? You don't feel like it is. You feel like you should make up for it by *scrutinizing* him extra carefully...
Logic: This one's *gone*. Make up somehow, connect something else, fast!
Half Light: A strange, uncalled for rage he seems to have no control over.
Esprit de Corps: One more down.
Kim Kitsuragi: In the silence, the lieutenant draws a line in his notes. Then nods at you once more.
Visual Calculus: The bruises. You can't make that out in a scope...
Kim Kitsuragi: "A red haired woman? Ruby..."

Shivers: Midtown, across the bay of Revachol. The oceanic wind washes forty-story towers. Above them -- Lausanne Central Aerodrome; a cocoon suspended in the sky by a web of suspension wiring, encircled by hybrid aircraft.
The Deserter: "She'd look -- at night, crying or smoking on the roof -- staring right into me..." He adds, to no one in particular: "It doesn't matter."
Shivers: Across the harbour, on the banks of the River Esperance, cold rain falls on Precinct 57 -- a two story box of duraluminum near the gates to Terminal H.
Shivers: Across the harbour, on the South bank of the River Esperance, white snow falls on a two story box of duraluminum. Precinct 57, near the gates to Terminal H.
The Deserter: "I've been through *all* of Martinaise -- every nook and cranny."
Reaction Speed: Thank god, the kid is picking it up...
The Deserter: "Wrinkled up whore," he nods.
Logic: That must be the representative of the Harbour company, who came in on her boat.
The Deserter: "No. Why would I do that? I didn't need tickets to Villiers... I put them back. If I wanted to extort someone I'd do better."
Rhetoric: This implies that he's thought about extorting her.
The Deserter: "I could see who she was, too," he nods. "A spook. On the run. Revachol's the cloaca of capital now. All the bagmen and arms dealers end up here. To do drugs and have sex like animals."
You: One little thing missed and I drown in anxiety...
You: No. It's cool. I've already got him. I don't need to be perfect.
Empathy: A brief flash of terror.
The Deserter: "What do you mean *put*?" He raises his eyes. They're round and wide.
The Deserter: "No one gives a *shit* what you think," the old man spits in the ash. "You and your cronies kill ten working class men a day. I've heard the statistics on Channel 8."
Composure: And inexplicably. It doesn't go with his pained voice.
Reaction Speed: And the fact that she was a *spook*. How did he come to that?
You: "And the bruises -- you could see her bruises through the scope of a rifle?"
The Deserter: "At night, crying or smoking on the roof. Like she knew I was here..." He says to no one in particular: "It doesn't matter."
The Deserter: "Locked up with your masters, like I'll be... maybe we'll meet?" He looks to the city. "She kept staring into the scope, you know -- in the end. Like she *knew*."
The Deserter: "Staring at the island, the fort, like she knew I was here..." He adds, to no one in particular: "It doesn't matter."
Perception (Hearing): You hear a low frequency hiss, barely. Beneath the audible spectrum. Then it's gone.
Esprit de Corps: As the men go, Patrol Officer Minot looks back over her shoulder -- at the crumbling fortification in the rain, like a rotten tooth rising out of the water...
Cuno: "Yeah, but that one too, right? Secret Whirling shit?"
The Deserter: "Yes, that too." He shakes his head, almost in awe. "The things they did in that little room. What she'd *do* to feel good..." He explains: "Funny, the way light works..."
You: "One more thing about this woman..."
The Deserter: "I don't understand..." He shakes his head.
Reaction Speed: Thank god, the lieutenant is picking it up...
The Deserter: "Yes," he looks at the charred logs. "I don't know why I do the things I do anymore."

The Deserter: "And I wanted her to see his head explode," he nods. "That too. She should know better than to hold a child murderer between her thighs. I knew he'd be there for one more second, *writhing*..."

The Deserter: "That's all it takes for the bullet to reach his head." He squints. "Now that I think of it, I wasn't aiming for his mouth. I wanted his brains to spill out on her... but..." he shrugs, "you can't have everything."
The Deserter: "Her..." He repeats, staring at the ashes -- then the reeds. There's a twitch in the corner of his eye.
You: "You wanted to punish her, so you killed him."
The Deserter: "In the water, behind the camp site there," he waves erratically toward the coast. "I don't remember precisely. It was in the winter. It was cold out..."
The Deserter: "I've seen her like that, yes," he nods. "Cutting those drugs of hers into little lines with a knife, masturbating..."
The Deserter: "Oh yes," he smacks his lips. "Cutting those drugs of hers into little lines with a knife, masturbating..."

The Deserter: "I got that open a long time ago. Some bourgeois game-merchant lived there -- I don't know... fifteen years ago? He left spare keys all over and I took one. Then I saw her turn the light on one night in my scope..." He points toward the Whirling-in-Rags.
You: "And the door? The steel door in the kitchen, how do you open that?"
You: "How did you get *in* there? The hidden pinball workshop?"
The Deserter: "I have my ways." A cracked smile appears on his dried white lips.
Logic: No it's not. Fix this now! Move on extra carefully! Be incredibly *minute*!
You: "I just got this feeling. From what you said. Do you agree?"
The Deserter: "If you came ten years ago, I would have killed you." He wipes his eye.
The Deserter: "*Twisted* by psychopharmaceuticals, alcohol, and the class interests of the bourgeoisie. They all are -- women nowadays..." He raises his eyes from the ashes.
Perception (Hearing): You hear a low frequency hiss, barely beneath the audible spectrum. Then it's gone.

Esprit de Corps: Special consultant Heidelstam is optimistic: "We'll see the boat when he comes. Let's go get a coffee until then. I know this interesting little place, where..." His voice trails off as the three walk down the jetty.
Shivers: Across the harbour, on the South bank of the River Esperance, the air stands still outside Precinct 57 -- a two story box of duraluminum near the gates to Terminal H.
Cuno: "You've been through some secret route shit, huh? *Inside* the Whirling-in-Rags, creepin' around?"
Cuno: "We can totally get more out of him..." the kid whispers. "He's squeelin'..."

The Deserter: "Since she came to Martinaise. I saw her sneaking in the reeds early in the morning, behind the Feld building. It was dark, still winter. She didn't have her skimpy outfit on then, just a spot in the night, moving..."
The Deserter: "Her..." he repeats, with strange slowness.
You: "Was that why you left the dried flowers behind her window?"

The Deserter: "Barely alive. They like to kill while they're on their drugs. After the landing, in the burning years I would take shots at them, *end* them. The worst ones. If I had a bullet to spare."
Electrochemistry: Everything in him fills with impossible longing, all at once.
You: "Let's talk about something else for now."
The Deserter: He draws shallow breaths.
Reaction Speed: One little thing -- what was her *name*, on the passport. Just curious...

The Deserter: "I did." He almost smiles. "She had a face like an archipelago, with those birthmarks. And a body, hard and lean and bruised all over -- black and yellow. I could see she's taken a beating."
The Deserter: "It was something else..." He stutters. "I don't remember. It was dark that morning. I only remember her face on the photo."
"It was something..." He stutters. "I don't remember. It was dark that morning. I only remember her face on the photo."
Reaction Speed: It quickly comes to you.
The secret path. He could have just *changed* his shoes, the prints in the dust were his!
You: "And you brought her May bells?"
Kim Kitsuragi: In the silence, the lieutenant draws a line in his notes.
The Deserter: "I was there one night and she was crying. Like a child, in the corner of her room -- on the floor. I'd never seen her do that before."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant nods at you, in acknowledgement.
Esprit de Corps: That's it. Motive. We have it.

Esprit de Corps: There, on a dilapidated jetty in a nameless village, two police officers and one special consultant look across a narrow strip of sea. The ruins of a seafort stick out of the water, built by Filippe II, re-appropriated by the Commune, then lost in the Landing...
Shivers: ...and knows it's over. They've come for her. Outside the dusk gathers, the river flows by, gold and orange into the Bay of Martinaise.

The Deserter: "Lax sexual morals are a bourgeois ploy," he gargles a spit ball. "As to pederasty, the Party legalized it in '04. My Party, not your liberal masters." He spits it out on the dying coals.
Empathy: While he stands here and rots.
You: "And by that you mean the representative of the harbour company?"
Volition: This man has seen past her, like you did.
You: "How long had you been watching her?"
Drama: He's setting it up for you...
The Deserter: "I'm not blind, am I?" He shakes his silver head.
You: "How did you get close enough to see the bruises, Mr. Dros?"
You: "And you could see her bruises -- through the scope of a rifle?"
You: This has got nothing to do with that. (Try to forget it.)
Inland Empire: It's no good, Harry. Her voice rings in the evening air. It smells of burning buildings...
Jump to: [The Deserter: "The old man raises his gaze. Someth..."]
The Deserter: "I know she's gone." He looks to the city. "Locked up, or on the run.... She kept staring into the scope, you know. In the end, this last week. At the fort. Like she *knew*."
You: "So in conclusion, it wasn't about him. It was about *her*." (Conclude.)
You: "This is the hidden buoy she told us about... You looked into it?"
Electrochemistry: Her body sweating from the drugs, slick from cerebral haemorrhage.
The Deserter: "Her passport. And tickets to Villiers." He coughs. "And from there to Casherbrume."
Kim Kitsuragi: "You had to open the steel door in the kitchen? How?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "You've been through the secret route behind the Whirling-in-Rags." The lieutenant interrupts.

The Deserter: "I've been through *all* of Martinaise -- every nook and cranny."
Pain Threshold: A little pain there. A prick.
Inland Empire: Dive for other clues now, like you always do. Make it up in the deep end...
Empathy: A bitter taste on his tongue.
You: "You saw through her? So did I."

Esprit de Corps: Across the water, on a dilapidated jetty in a nameless village -- made of grey cinder block houses with eternite roofs -- two police officers and one special consultant look across a narrow strip of sea.
The Deserter: "Them fucking..." He looks at the charred wood. "I didn't like that."
Kim Kitsuragi: "One more thing -- the flowers, Mr. Dros. The dried flowers that were on the roof."
Kim Kitsuragi: "Did you make that hole?"
The Deserter: "With a clip point knife."

The Deserter: The old man raises his gaze. Something glimmers in the corner of his black eye...

Encyclopedia: In the Free State of Semenine. Hidden away at the edge of the Earth, near the pale.
You: "You saw her name on the passport. But before, when I said her name is *Klaasje* -- you didn't seem to recognize it."
The Deserter: "The sun came up and her hair was like cobwebs. She smoked more fags and snorted a line of whatever *shit* she was on. Right there..." he shakes his head. "She needed it just to move."
Perception (Hearing): Good for listening in too. For hearing the moaning and the snorts.
The Deserter: "No..." He starts to shake his head again, a sunflower on a withered stalk.

You: "You mean the Wild Pines representative again, right?"
You: "The bruises on her body -- any chance you've seen them through a *hole in a wall?*"
Conceptualization: For him to stop reacting to stimuli, to be broken off from the world. Cordoned into darkness.
Composure: There it is again. The strange neurological state he's sometimes in.
Drama: Safe and sound, sire. Surely you have not misplaced the witness.
The Deserter: "Herding the strikebreakers like that -- I kept an eye on them." He stares inland, then back at you.
You: "By that you mean Joyce Messier, the Wild Pines rep?"
Suggestion: He wants to see her covered in blood.
Half Light: A sudden pang of rage.
The Deserter: He draws shallow breaths.
The Deserter: *Splat*, a bloody spitball lands on the firewood.

Reaction Speed: Wait, she was a *spook*? How did he come to that?
